19th Avenue, north from 58th Street. In the right foreground is a New York City highway department storage yard, at 57th Street. In view 2, in back of the yard, is visible part of Washington Cemetery. The dwellings seen in view 3 are numbers 5509 to 5413; view 4 shows the west side of the avenue and the garage of the Department of Sanitation.

January 21, 1935
